cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper addresses the problem of efficiently evaluating target functional dependencies in the Data Exchange process, which is a core problem in database management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Database). The paper also proposes a novel chase-based algorithm that exploits the interactions between source-to-target tuple-generating dependencies and target fds, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm also leads to interesting parallelization opportunities, which relates to distributed systems (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
